# Tone Function on Buzzer

This project demonstrates the use of a piezo buzzer to generate sound using the `tone()` function. Different frequencies can be played to produce audible tones, making it useful for alarms, notifications, and simple melodies.

## Components Used
- Arduino/ESP32
- Piezo Buzzer
- Breadboard & Jumper Wires

## Features
- Generates tones at specified frequencies.
- Demonstrates use of the `tone()` function.
